caption.p: The viability of HepG2 cells exposed to the tested honeys for 24 h (black), 48 h (grey) and 72 h (whitist) incubation. Results are the mean ± SD of four replicates. *, **, *** signifies p ≤ 0.05 vs. control (0% honey) after 24 h, 48 h, and 72 h incubation, respectively, analyzed by one-way ANOVA followed by Duncan’s multiple comparison test. ( A): Analogue, ( B): manuka; ( C): arjuna, ( D): guggul, ( E): jiaogulan, ( F): olive honey.
